article.headline: Ill.-Chicago 76, Wis.-Green Bay 67
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Guard Josh Mayo scored a game-high 32 points, including six 3-pointers, to lead Illinois-Chicago past Wisconsin-Green Bay 76-67 Saturday in Horizon League action at the UIC Pavilion. No other starters for the Flames (5-4, 2-0) managed to score in double digits, though Robert Kreps came off the bench to score 14 for Illinois-Chicago. The Flames, who took a 37-26 lead into halftime, shot 49 percent (24-of-49) from the field for the game; Wisconsin-Green Bay shot 36.5 percent (23-of-63). The Flames made 45 percent of their 3-point attempts (9-of-20), while the Phoenix made just 14.3 percent (2-of-14). Mike Schachtner led Wisconsin-Green Bay (6-3, 1-1) in scoring with 24 points; Randy Berry added 16. With Saturday's win, the Flames remain unbeaten at home this season.
